# clinical-ops-copilot — standing rules

## Stack
- Typed Python 3.11+ project using `uv` for environment and dependencies.
- All data models use Pydantic.
- No secrets in code; use environment variables only.

## Testing & style
- Every module gets tests. Prefer small, composable functions.

## Architecture (target)
- Two MCP servers: `clinical-data` (read-side) and `clinic-ops` (action-side).
- Agent host: MCP client + orchestrator.
- Human approval UI.
- Evals package.

## Working style
- Work in small, verifiable steps.
- After each change, write or update a test and tell the exact command to run it.
- Do not move on until the test passes.
- Always show the diff and explain design choices.
- Never invent MCP SDK APIs — ask to paste the relevant docs if unsure.
